    "**Insight:** Rainfall data was aggregated from individual observations into a county-month level dataset to align with the IPC food insecurity assessments. Mean rainfall indicators were calculated, including short-term rainfall conditions (rfq_mean), 3-month cumulative rainfall anomalies (r3q_mean), and 1-month rainfall anomalies (r1q_mean). The inclusion of multiple rainfall windows allows the model to capture both immediate rainfall shocks and longer-term moisture conditions that affect agricultural productivity. Aggregating at county-month level reduces daily/point-level variability while preserving the climate signals relevant to food security outcomes.\n",
