    "**Rainfall anomaly vs Crisis**\n",
    "The comparison between rainfall conditions and IPC crisis outcomes shows that counties experiencing food insecurity crises generally have lower rainfall anomaly values compared to non-crisis periods. This supports the original hypothesis that rainfall deficits act as an early warning signal for food insecurity because reduced rainfall can negatively affect crop production, pasture availability, and water resources.\n",
